cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper investigates the effect of network width on learned features in neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and specifically deep learning. The use of activation atlases to visualize learned features suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. The emphasis on transferability of learned features suggests a focus on general machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) tasks. Finally, the use of wide networks and their impact on information capacity suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
